properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 9 at 2:52AM PST until February 9 at 3:00PM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, north winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and very rough waters expected. For the
Small Craft Advisory, north winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to
40 kt and rough waters expected.

* WHERE...San Pablo Bay, Suisun Bay, the West Delta and the San
Francisco Bay north of the Bay Bridge.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 7 AM this morning to 3 PM
PST this afternoon. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 7 AM
PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
